instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The system adopts a modular, service‑oriented architecture where a central Digital Twin Framework hub orchestrates bidirectional data exchange between enriched BIM models and the physical building’s sensor fleet, while exposing standardized extension points for custom analytics and service integration. Runtime configuration management allows the framework to adapt to evolving operational needs without full redeployment, providing dynamic orchestration and resource management across the Digital Twin lifecycle."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Phases: 1) Initial device modeling directly within BIM, defining sensors, actuators, and controller logic; 2) Transformation via Model‑Driven Engineering (MDE) principles to extract structured representations; 3) Automatic generation of deployable DT artifacts with minimal manual intervention; 4) Real‑time bidirectional data exchange ensuring continuous synchronization; 5) Interactive visualization and monitoring; 6) Extension of functionality through custom services via standardized extension points. Transitions are managed through automated artifact extraction and deployment pipelines, with governance enforced by verification against the enriched BIM baseline."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model fidelity is preserved by validating enriched BIM models against a set of structural and semantic rules during the validation step of the conversion pipeline. Eclipse Ditto’s policy engine performs continuous verification of incoming sensor data and actuator commands, ensuring that all values respect predefined bounds and units. Fault tolerance is achieved through Eclipse Hono’s at‑least‑once message delivery guarantee and Ditto’s persistent event storage, providing resilience against network interruptions. Error detection is handled by policy violations that trigger alerts or message rejections, while error correction is achieved by either resetting the device state or reverting to the last stable state stored in Ditto. Quality assurance of the DT system is supported by the modular architecture, which enables adding custom analytics services to monitor fidelity metrics and enforce consistency between the physical assets and their digital twins.}"
]

